com.motorolasolutions.mpact.mpactclient

Class MPactClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.motorolasolutions.mpact.mpactclient.MPactClient

  • public class MPactClient
extends java.lang.Object
    A class used to set up interaction with the MPact Server from an Activity or Service. This class is used in conjunction with MPactClientConsumer interface.

      • getInstanceForApplication

        public static MPactClient getInstanceForApplication(android.content.Context context)
        An accessor for the singleton instance of this class. A context must be provided, but if you need to use it from a non-Activity or non-Service class, you can attach it to another singleton or a subclass of the Android Application class.

      • bind

        public void bind(MPactClientConsumer consumer)
        Binds an Android Activity or Service to the MPactService. The Activity or Service must implement the MPactClientConsumer interface so that it can get a callback when the service is ready to use.
        Parameters:
        consumer - the Activity or Service that will receive the callback when the service is ready.

      • unBind

        public void unBind(MPactClientConsumer consumer)
        Unbinds an Android Activity or Service to the MPactService. This should typically be called in the onDestroy() method.
        Parameters:
        consumer - the Activity or Service that no longer needs to use the service.

      • isBound

        public boolean isBound(MPactClientConsumer consumer)
        Tells you if the passed MPactClientConsumer is bound to the service
        Parameters:
        consumer -
        Returns:
        true if the consumer is bound to the service.

      • setNotifier

        public void setNotifier(MPactClientNotifier notifier)
        Specifies a class that should be called each time the MPactService has a notification that should be sent. IMPORTANT: Only one MPactClientNotifier may be active for a given application. If two different activities or services set different MPactClientNotifier instances, the last one set will receive all the notifications.
        Parameters:
        notifier -
        See Also:
        MPactClientNotifier, Start()
